<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="16">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="16">Marquesas Islands, known only from the type locality on Ua Huka in the Hane/Hokatu cliff zone at the head of the valley above Hane village.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="11" pageNumber="16" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="16">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="11" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lorence &amp; W. L. Wagner" authorityYear="2011" class="Bryopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="16" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="uahukaense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="16">Polystichum uahukaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely localized and known from a single population on moist, mossy cliff faces in shade of wet forest with 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="11" pageNumber="16" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tiliaceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="16">Hibiscus tiliaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pandanales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tectorius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">
<pageBreakToken pageId="12" pageNumber="17" start="start">Pandanus</pageBreakToken>
tectorius
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dominant, at 520-525 m. Associated vegetation on cliffs includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sch Bip" authorityYear="1856" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Asteraceae" genus="Bidens" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Campanulales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="polycephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Bidens polycephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sch. Bip., 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Boehmeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Boehmeria virgata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" genus="Macropiper" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Piperales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Macropiper latifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L. f.) Miq., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" genus="Peperomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Piperales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Peperomia pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(G. Forst.) A. Dietr., 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Leiothrichidae" genus="Phyllanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Passeriformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Phyllanthus pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müll">Muell</normalizedToken>
. Arg., and pteridophyes including 
<taxonomicName genus="Dryopters" lsidName="" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="macropholis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Dryopters macropholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. B. Andrews" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Langsd. &amp; Fisch." class="Filicopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Microsorum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Polypodiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="grossum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Microsorum grossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Langsd. &amp; Fisch.) Brownlie
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">, Nephrolepis</emphasis>
sp., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Forst" authorityYear="1786" class="Pteridopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Filicales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Polypodiophyta" rank="species" species="comans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="17">Pteris comans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
G. Forst., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spring" authorityYear="1843" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." class="Lycopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Selaginellales" pageId="12" pageNumber="17" phylum="Lycophyta" rank="species" species="arbuscula">
